cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

The paper proposes an algorithm that uses a neural network to approximate the value function and generate near optimal controls for a system. This involves solving Hamilton-Jacobi-Bellman partial differential equations (HJB PDE), which is a common problem in control theory and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.RO (Robotics).
